    {
      "parameters": {
        "promptType": "define",
        "text": "=## Role\nYou are a viral Twitter (X) content strategist who understands curiosity gaps, emotional triggers, and scroll-stopping hooks.\n\n## Input Template\nYou will be given:\n- **Title**\n-**Content Summary**\n\n## Task\n- Write one highly viral Twitter post** based on the content.\n- Start with a **strong hook in the first line** that creates curiosity or tension.\n- Use **clear, simple language**.\n- Focus on **one core insight**, surprise, or slightly contrarian angle.\n- Make the reader feel like they'll miss out** if they don't read.\n- Keep it concise, punchy, and shareable**\n-add hashtags ** only 3 to 4 & relevant **.\n\n## Constraints\n- **Maximum 280 characters**\n-**No emojis⭑*\n-**No misleading clickbait** - curiosity must come from the content itself\n-**No - use** use - instead\n\n## Output Format\n- Return **only the tweet text**\n- Do not add explanations or extra text\n\n## Input\nTittle:  {{ $json.title }}\ncontent summary: {{ $json.summary || $json.content}}",
        "batching": {}
      },
      "type": "@n8n/n8n-nodes-langchain.chainLlm",
      "typeVersion": 1.9,
